<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Module 7</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css"><script>MathJax = {tex: {inlineMath: [['\\(','\\)']], displayMath: [['$$','$$']]}}; </script><script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script><script src="../js/navigation.js"></script><script src="../js/problems.js"></script><script src="../js/quizzes.js"></script></head><body><header><div class="header-content"><h1>MODULE 7: KINEMATICS</h1><p class="subtitle">Forward/Inverse Kinematics, Jacobian</p></div></header><main class="container"><div class="progress-container"><div class="progress-bar"></div><div class="progress-text">0% Complete</div></div><section class="content-section"><h2>Module Overview</h2><p>Kinematics determines how joint angles map to end-effector positions (FK) and what joint angles achieve desired positions (IK). Essential for gait planning.</p><div class="important-box"><h3>Forward Kinematics</h3><p>Given \(\vec{\theta}\), compute \(\vec{x}: \vec{x} = f_{FK}(\vec{\theta}).\) Maps joint to task space.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Inverse Kinematics</h3><p>Given \(\vec{x}_{desired},\), compute \(\vec{\theta}: \vec{\theta} = f_{IK}^{-1}(\vec{x}_{desired}).\) Mapping from task to joint space.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Jacobian</h3><p>\(\dot{x} = J\dot{\theta}.\) Relates joint velocities to end-effector velocities. Singularity when \(\det(J) = 0.\)</p></div><section class="quiz-section"><h2>Module Quiz</h2><div id="quiz-container"></div><button class="submit" onclick="module7Quiz()">Submit Quiz</button><div id="quiz-results"></div></section><div class="nav-buttons"><button class="secondary" onclick="navigateTo('06-differential-equations.html')">Previous</button><button onclick="navigateTo('08-vibrations-waves.html')">Next</button></div></main><footer><p>Module 7</p></footer><script>function module7Quiz(){submitQuiz('07').percentage>=70&&markModuleComplete('07');}window.addEventListener("load",function(){updateProgressBar();});</script></body></html>
