cat > "$BASE/08-vibrations-waves.html" << 'EOF'
<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Module 8</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css"><script>MathJax = {tex: {inlineMath: [['\\(','\\)']], displayMath: [['$$','$$']]}}; </script><script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script><script src="../js/navigation.js"></script><script src="../js/problems.js"></script><script src="../js/quizzes.js"></script></head><body><header><div class="header-content"><h1>MODULE 8: VIBRATIONS & WAVES</h1><p class="subtitle">Free/Forced Vibrations, Resonance</p></div></header><main class="container"><div class="progress-container"><div class="progress-bar"></div><div class="progress-text">0% Complete</div></div><section class="content-section"><h2>Module Overview</h2><p>Vibrations affect hexapod structural integrity. Understanding natural frequency and resonance ensures safe operation without destructive oscillations.</p><div class="important-box"><h3>Free Vibration</h3><p>Natural frequency: \(\omega_n = \sqrt{k/m}.\) Underdamped (\(\zeta < 1\)) oscillates: \(x(t) = e^{-\zeta\omega_nt}(C_1\cos\omega_dt + C_2\sin\omega_dt).\)</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Forced Vibration</h3><p>\(m\ddot{x} + c\dot{x} + kx = F_0\cos(\omega t).\) Resonance when \(\omega \approx \omega_n\) causes large amplitude.</p></div><section class="quiz-section"><h2>Module Quiz</h2><div id="quiz-container"></div><button class="submit" onclick="module8Quiz()">Submit Quiz</button><div id="quiz-results"></div></section><div class="nav-buttons"><button class="secondary" onclick="navigateTo('07-kinematics.html')">Previous</button><button onclick="navigateTo('09-control-theory.html')">Next</button></div></main><footer><p>Module 8</p></footer><script>function module8Quiz(){submitQuiz('08').percentage>=70&&markModuleComplete('08');}window.addEventListener("load",function(){updateProgressBar();});</script></body></html>
EOF

cat > "$BASE/09-control-theory.html" << 'EOF'
<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Module 9</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css"><script>MathJax = {tex: {inlineMath: [['\\(','\\)']], displayMath: [['$$','$$']]}}; </script><script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script><script src="../js/navigation.js"></script><script src="../js/problems.js"></script><script src="../js/quizzes.js"></script></head><body><header><div class="header-content"><h1>MODULE 9: CONTROL THEORY</h1><p class="subtitle">Linear Systems, PID Control, Stability</p></div></header><main class="container"><div class="progress-container"><div class="progress-bar"></div><div class="progress-text">0% Complete</div></div><section class="content-section"><h2>Module Overview</h2><p>Control theory enables hexapods to track trajectories. PID control is standard. Stability analysis ensures safe operation. Frequency-domain design provides insight.</p><div class="important-box"><h3>PID Control</h3><p>\(u = K_p e + K_i\int e dt + K_d de/dt.\) Proportional responds to error, integral eliminates steady-state, derivative adds damping.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Stability</h3><p>All poles in left half-plane (LHP) = stable. Any pole in right half-plane (RHP) = unstable. Poles on imaginary axis = marginally stable.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Frequency Response</h3><p>Bode plots: magnitude 20log|G(jw)| and phase vs frequency. Gain margin > 6 dB, phase margin > 30° typical.</p></div><section class="quiz-section"><h2>Module Quiz</h2><div id="quiz-container"></div><button class="submit" onclick="module9Quiz()">Submit Quiz</button><div id="quiz-results"></div></section><div class="nav-buttons"><button class="secondary" onclick="navigateTo('08-vibrations-waves.html')">Previous</button><button onclick="navigateTo('10-fluid-mechanics.html')">Next</button></div></main><footer><p>Module 9</p></footer><script>function module9Quiz(){submitQuiz('09').percentage>=70&&markModuleComplete('09');}window.addEventListener("load",function(){updateProgressBar();});</script></body></html>
