cat > "$BASE/10-fluid-mechanics.html" << 'EOF'
<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Module 10</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css"><script>MathJax = {tex: {inlineMath: [['\\(','\\)']], displayMath: [['$$','$$']]}}; </script><script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script><script src="../js/navigation.js"></script><script src="../js/problems.js"></script><script src="../js/quizzes.js"></script></head><body><header><div class="header-content"><h1>MODULE 10: FLUID MECHANICS</h1><p class="subtitle">Bernoulli, Reynolds Number, Drag</p></div></header><main class="container"><div class="progress-container"><div class="progress-bar"></div><div class="progress-text">0% Complete</div></div><section class="content-section"><h2>Module Overview</h2><p>While less directly applicable to terrestrial hexapods, fluid mechanics informs hydraulic actuation and drag. Bernoulli equation governs energy conservation in fluid flow.</p><div class="important-box"><h3>Bernoulli Equation</h3><p>$\(p + \frac{1}{2}\rho v^2 + \rho gh = \text{constant}.\) Pressure + dynamic + gravitational potential along streamline.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Reynolds Number</h3><p>\(Re = \rho v L/\mu.\) \(Re < 2300\): laminar. \(Re > 4000\): turbulent. Ratio of inertial to viscous forces.</p></div><div class="important-box"><h3>Drag Force</h3><p>\(F_D = \frac{1}{2}C_D \rho A v^2.\) Aerodynamic drag increases with \(v^2\).</p></div><section class="quiz-section"><h2>Module Quiz</h2><div id="quiz-container"></div><button class="submit" onclick="module10Quiz()">Submit Quiz</button><div id="quiz-results"></div></section><div class="nav-buttons"><button class="secondary" onclick="navigateTo('09-control-theory.html')">Previous</button><button onclick="navigateTo('11-thermodynamics.html')">Next</button></div></main><footer><p>Module 10</p></footer><script>function module10Quiz(){submitQuiz('10').percentage>=70&&markModuleComplete('10');}window.addEventListener("load",function(){updateProgressBar();});</script></body></html>
EOF

